abla, \overline{
abla}$ and $	ilde{
abla}$, respectively. Given a differentiable curve $\alpha : (-\varepsilon, \varepsilon) 	o M$ with $\alpha(0) = p$ and $\alpha'(0) = v \in T_p M$, how can I "explicitly" calculate $\overline{
abla}_v \alpha'$ in terms of the well known derivatives in $\mathbb{R}^{n+1}$? Is it true that $	ilde{
abla}_v \alpha' = \alpha''(0)$, so that $$ \overline{
